In Odoo 17, scheduled actions (also known as cron jobs) allow you to automate tasks that need to run at specific intervals. Here\rquote s how to set up and manage scheduled actions:\par
\par
Creating a Scheduled Action\par
Activate Developer Mode:\par
\par
Go to Settings.\par
Scroll down and click on Activate Developer Mode.\par
Navigate to Scheduled Actions:\par
\par
Go to Settings > Technical > Automation > Scheduled Actions.\par
Create a New Scheduled Action:\par
\par
Click on Create.\par
Fill in the following fields:\par
Name: A descriptive name for the action.\par
Model: Select the model on which the action will operate (e.g., res.partner).\par
Action To Do: Choose the action type (e.g., Python code, server action).\par
Interval Number: Set how often the action will run (e.g., every hour, day).\par
Interval Type: Define the unit of time (Minutes, Hours, Days, etc.).\par
Next Execution Date: Set the next date/time for the action to run.\par
Number of Calls: Set how many times the action should run.\par
Active: Ensure this box is checked to enable the action.\par
Define the Action:\par
\par
If you selected a Python code action, write the code you want to execute.\par
For server actions, select or create the action you want to automate.\par
Save: Click Save to apply your changes.\par
\par
Managing Scheduled Actions\par
Editing: You can return to the list of scheduled actions to edit or deactivate any existing actions.\par
Testing: You can manually trigger the scheduled action by clicking on Run Manually (if available).\par
Logs: Check execution logs to monitor the status and troubleshoot any issues. Logs can be found under Settings > Technical > Automation > Scheduled Actions > Logs.\par
Common Use Cases\par
Automated Emails: Sending periodic reports or reminders.\par
Data Cleanup: Regularly archiving or deleting old records.\par
Notifications: Reminding users of tasks or updates based on specific conditions.\par
Conclusion\par
Scheduled actions in Odoo 17 are a powerful tool for automating repetitive tasks, enhancing efficiency, and ensuring that important actions are not overlooked. By setting them up properly, you can streamline various operations in your business.\par
